05:12.771 --> 05:14.856
so miss westervelt couldn't...
This is miss...

05:15.941 --> 05:16.942
I'm Margot.

05:17.025 --> 05:18.865
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- (Tyler clears throat)

05:23.198 --> 05:25.492
Margot. Welcome.

05:26.076 --> 05:29.454
We'll endeavor to make your evening
as pleasant as possible.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.248
- Thanks.
- Right this way.

05:31.331 --> 05:32.332
Thanks.

05:33.375 --> 05:34.918
Oh, my god. I'm so sorry.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.771
That was really awkward.
I'm sorry. That was not...

05:36.795 --> 05:38.588
- No, no. Fine.
- (Sighs)

05:38.672 --> 05:39.673
Don't worry about it.

05:40.131 --> 05:41.841
Tyler: (Clears throat) Sorry.

05:45.095 --> 05:47.681
Elsa: Mr. Leibrandt.
Mrs. Leibrandt. Welcome.

05:47.764 --> 05:49.951
Richard: We'll just go straight
to the restaurant, if you don't mind.

05:49.975 --> 05:52.561
Anne: We've seen the tour
many, many times.

05:52.644 --> 05:53.895
Elsa: Yes, yes, you have.

05:54.688 --> 05:58.149
My esteemed guests
can continue their conversation this way.

05:58.233 --> 06:00.360
Thank you. Please follow me.

06:01.152 --> 06:03.613
So, like, what are you working on now?

06:03.697 --> 06:06.032
Oh, hey, thanks for asking.
See, people still know me.

06:06.491 --> 06:08.868
I'm moving into
the presenter phase of my career.

06:08.952 --> 06:10.412
You know? Do me.

06:12.539 --> 06:19.337
Elsa: Hawthorn island
comprises 12 acres of forest and pasture.

06:19.421 --> 06:21.965
We have the bounty
of the sea surrounding us.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.049
Oh, yeah, right.

06:23.133 --> 06:26.344
Out there, right now,
we are harvesting scallops.

06:26.428 --> 06:27.470
You'll eat them tonight.

06:27.554 --> 06:29.514
- No, get out. Oh, shoot!
- Yes.

06:29.598 --> 06:31.433
Hey! (Laughing)

06:31.516 --> 06:33.852
Hey, harvest harder, me dude!

06:33.935 --> 06:35.270
We're starving!

06:35.353 --> 06:36.479
(All laughing)

06:36.563 --> 06:37.814
Oh, my goodness.

06:37.897 --> 06:41.818
I do like the sense of it
being a sort of biome of culinary ideas.

06:41.901 --> 06:44.362
Right. Like, it functions like
an epicurean salon.

06:44.904 --> 06:46.781
No, I like biome better I think.

06:46.865 --> 06:48.384
Biome's better. Yeah, yeah.
I mean, that's... yeah.

06:48.408 --> 06:51.703
Margot: We have reached
the base camp of mount bullshit.

06:51.786 --> 06:53.038
This is insane. (Chuckles)

06:53.121 --> 06:54.956
(Dramatic music playing)

07:00.920 --> 07:01.921
Smell that.

07:02.589 --> 07:03.590
Both: Mmm.

07:06.635 --> 07:07.802
Soren: We're gonna be hungry.

07:07.886 --> 07:09.488
George: Yeah, I'm a huge
embarrassing foodie.

07:09.512 --> 07:10.597
I love this stuff.

07:10.680 --> 07:12.724
And I'm close, personal
friends with the chef.

07:12.807 --> 07:13.933
Soren: Okay, player.

07:14.017 --> 07:16.645
Elsa: Our smokehouse
is in the nordic tradition.

07:17.062 --> 07:19.773
We use the meat of dairy cows only,

07:20.982 --> 07:26.738
which we age for an astonishing 152 days
to relax the protein strands.

07:26.821 --> 07:29.074
Bryce: Ah, yes. Yes.
Ted: Can we pop in here?

07:29.491 --> 07:31.761
- Dude, I read about one of these online.
- Oh, yeah? Can I check it out?

07:31.785 --> 07:32.887
- Dave: Korean barbeque.
- Yes.

07:32.911 --> 07:35.246
But please, do not touch our proteins.
They're immature.

07:35.330 --> 07:38.166
So, what happens if
you serve it on the 153rd day?

07:38.249 --> 07:40.335
Does all hell break loose, or...

07:40.418 --> 07:43.004
Well, I suppose the bacteria
would introduce itself

07:43.088 --> 07:46.591
to the consumer's bloodstream
and spread into their spinal membranes,

07:46.675 --> 07:49.177
after which point, he or she
would become incapacitated

07:49.260 --> 07:50.970
and shortly thereafter expire.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.264
So, yes, all hell would break loose.

07:53.556 --> 07:56.059
(All chuckle nervously)

07:56.142 --> 07:57.477
Good thing we're pros, yes?

07:59.646 --> 08:00.706
George: I'd like to work for her.

08:00.730 --> 08:01.731
Soren: Yeah. Dave: Cool.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.108
Elsa: This is where we live.

08:04.442 --> 08:08.071
Bryce: Yeah? What, you actually live here?
All of you?

08:08.613 --> 08:09.698
Elsa: All of us.

08:09.781 --> 08:10.949
Except chef.

08:11.032 --> 08:12.701
- Yeah, well...
- Lillian: Oof.

08:13.535 --> 08:14.953
<i>Esprit de corps.</i> No?

08:15.036 --> 08:17.956
Elsa: No, Mr. Feldman.
It's very much more than that.

08:18.873 --> 08:20.125
Here we are family.

08:20.458 --> 08:23.128
Each day starts at 6:00,
with five hours of prep work.

08:23.211 --> 08:25.171
We harvest. We ferment.

08:25.588 --> 08:27.549
We slaughter. We marinate.

08:28.091 --> 08:30.135
We liquify. We spherify.

08:30.552 --> 08:31.761
We gel.

08:31.845 --> 08:33.429
- They, um... they "gel?"
- Yeah.

08:33.513 --> 08:34.514
We gel.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.933
Dinner is typically
four hours and 25 minutes.

08:38.017 --> 08:39.936
Each day ends at well past
2:00 in the morning.

08:40.019 --> 08:41.580
So yes, it's best that we all live here.

08:41.604 --> 08:43.148
You guys ever get burned out, or...

08:43.773 --> 08:46.651
- "Burned out?"
- Yeah, sorry, sorry.

08:46.735 --> 08:49.446
Like, tired of doing the same thing?

08:49.529 --> 08:52.490
Chef holds himself
to the highest standard, and so do we.

08:53.742 --> 08:57.412
We never burn anything unless by design,
to make delicious.

08:58.163 --> 09:00.331
Now, who's hungry?

09:01.332 --> 09:02.768
Margot: There is food
at the end of this, right?

09:02.792 --> 09:04.419
Ted: Boat food to dinner table.

09:04.502 --> 09:05.795
Elsa.

09:05.879 --> 09:06.921
Excuse me.

09:07.338 --> 09:08.757
Elsa. Elsa, hi.

09:08.840 --> 09:09.841
Uh, who lives there?

09:10.425 --> 09:11.426
Chef.

09:11.509 --> 09:12.761
Oh, can we see that?

09:14.804 --> 09:18.057
Even we are not allowed
inside chef's cottage, Mr. Ledford.

09:21.478 --> 09:22.937
Margot: (Shushes) Come on.

09:23.021 --> 09:26.149
We mustn't disturb
the lord high emperor of sustenance.

09:26.232 --> 09:27.275
Yeah, all right.

09:28.193 --> 09:29.879
Isn't the goat the greatest of
all time, though?

09:29.903 --> 09:31.321
No, no, no. Back in the day...

09:32.113 --> 09:33.753
George: You think he'd pick that big guy?

09:34.824 --> 09:37.160
(Indistinct chatter and laughter)

09:38.661 --> 09:41.039
So, I think that maybe
we'll just time the post.

09:41.122 --> 09:42.874
Oh, yeah? Bring you to the best spots?

09:42.957 --> 09:44.393
Felicity: Yes, well,
I book the best spots.

09:44.417 --> 09:45.603
- So you tell me.
- George: With my name.

09:45.627 --> 09:46.669
Felicity: Well, I...

09:48.838 --> 09:49.881
Hi, again.

09:49.964 --> 09:51.132
Bryce: Gentlemen, parfait?

09:52.133 --> 09:53.426
Felicity: Oh! Look at that view.

09:54.385 --> 09:55.512
Wanna take a picture?

09:55.595 --> 09:57.388
(Classical music playing)

10:09.734 --> 10:10.944
(Indistinct chatter)

10:12.946 --> 10:14.197
Soren: Where we going, chief?

10:14.280 --> 10:16.491
Here. Switch seats with me.

10:17.158 --> 10:19.077
- Miss...
- Mills.

10:19.160 --> 10:22.413
Ms. Mills. You will be sitting
in miss westervelt's seat.

10:23.039 --> 10:24.600
Richard: Just...
You should have the better view.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.751
Anne: Well, I don't... (Stutters)

10:26.835 --> 10:28.253
I don't need a better view.

10:28.336 --> 10:29.396
Richard: No,
I'm gonna look at the kitchen.

10:29.420 --> 10:31.756
Margot: Thank you!
Richard: The rosé, we'll get first.

10:31.840 --> 10:32.841
Enjoy.

10:41.474 --> 10:45.228
Elsa: Feel free to observe
the cooks as they innovate.

10:46.938 --> 10:51.234
But please, do not photograph our dishes.

10:51.317 --> 10:54.279
Chef strongly feels that
the beauty in his creations

10:54.362 --> 10:56.197
lies in their ephemeral nature.

10:56.281 --> 10:57.699
Here, come on. We can't miss this.

10:59.200 --> 11:00.910
Margot: Oh. Um...

11:03.872 --> 11:05.415
Do you make that with a pacojet?

11:06.416 --> 11:08.084
- Exactly right, sir.
- Mmm.

11:08.668 --> 11:12.797
You know, a pacojet can produce
a powderized, uh, snow-like texture.

11:12.881 --> 11:15.174
- Cool.
- Yeah. I have one.

11:15.258 --> 11:17.176
You really know your stuff, Mr. Ledford.

11:18.511 --> 11:19.679
You know my name?

11:19.762 --> 11:21.723
Oh, we like to know
everyone who dines with us.

11:23.266 --> 11:25.327
And chef, is he around here somewhere?
I'd love to talk with him.

11:25.351 --> 11:26.853
Why don't you take your seat?

11:28.521 --> 11:29.522
We're about to serve.

11:30.440 --> 11:32.150
Oh, right. Yeah, okay. Thank you.

11:33.359 --> 11:34.545
- Tyler: Wow.
- More lambrusco, madam?

11:34.569 --> 11:36.905
Tyler: Well, the attention
to detail, it's like, fuck!

11:36.988 --> 11:38.072
And he knew my name, babe!

11:38.156 --> 11:39.675
Yeah. I noticed you didn't ask his name.

11:39.699 --> 11:40.700
Yeah, well, you know.

11:43.411 --> 11:44.412
(Shushes)

11:44.495 --> 11:45.496
Tyler: There he is.

11:57.592 --> 11:59.761
Fuck me. Is he looking at me?

12:06.267 --> 12:08.394
(Unsettling music playing)

12:18.321 --> 12:19.697
(Indistinct chatter)

12:22.283 --> 12:25.036
Ted: Bland? You call that bland?
Lillian: Well, it is bland.

12:25.119 --> 12:26.388
Soren: You like the winter, don't you?

12:26.412 --> 12:27.681
Dave: I don't actually...
Soren: Fucking freak.

12:27.705 --> 12:30.059
Server: Here we have a compressed
and pickled cucumber melon,

12:30.083 --> 12:31.918
milk snow, and charred lace.

12:32.001 --> 12:33.044
- Soren: Thanks.
- Enjoy.

12:34.796 --> 12:38.049
Oh! This ongoing obsession with snow.

12:38.132 --> 12:40.718
It's officially a plague,
and no one is immune.

12:45.556 --> 12:47.350
Can you taste a little goat?

12:47.850 --> 12:49.435
Right at the end. A little kid.

12:49.519 --> 12:50.561
She said milk.

12:51.187 --> 12:52.230
I wonder.

12:52.313 --> 12:54.333
- She did not say of what species.
- Ted: She did not.

12:54.357 --> 12:55.668
Felicity: I want to hear
your pitch for the show,

12:55.692 --> 12:58.069
but first I would like to say "thank you"

12:58.152 --> 13:00.130
- for the last two years.
- (Phone camera shutter clicks)

13:00.154 --> 13:02.073
Felicity: This opportunity has been, uh...

13:02.156 --> 13:03.356
George: The best of your life?

13:03.408 --> 13:04.909
Let's have to many, many, many more.

13:04.993 --> 13:07.388
